	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the point is to check for &gt;= and &lt; on signed numbers, similar to how you would use the carry <span class="posthilit">flag</span> to check for &gt;= and &lt; on unsigned numbers. The problem is that overflow will give an incorrect result.
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #$10&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 16<br /><span class="posthilit">cmp</span> #$F0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; -16<br />bpl IsGreaterThan&nbsp; &nbsp;; will branch, 16 &gt; -16<br /><br />lda #$10&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 16<br /><span class="posthilit">cmp</span> #$00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 0<br />bpl IsGreaterThan&nbsp; &nbsp;; will branch, 16 &gt; 0<br /><br />lda #$10&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 16<br /><span class="posthilit">cmp</span> #$20&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 32<br />bpl IsGreaterThan&nbsp; &nbsp;; will NOT branch, 16 &lt; 32<br /><br />; Overflow: 122 - &#40;-32&#41; = 154<br />lda #$70&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; 122<br /><span class="posthilit">cmp</span> #$E0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; -32<br />bpl IsGreaterThan&nbsp; &nbsp;; will NOT branch, even though 122 &gt; -32<br /></div>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


